Package: tin
Version: 1.4.5
Revision: 12
Depends: pcre
BuildDepends: ncurses-dev
Conflicts: tin-unstable
Replaces: tin-unstable
Source: ftp://ftp.tin.org/pub/news/clients/tin/stable/tin-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: fd4a8006f19020ed78c538f6c92f1027
ConfigureParams: --mandir='${prefix}/share/man' --sysconfdir=%p/etc/%n --with-install-prefix=%d --enable-nntp-only --with-defaults-dir=%p/etc/%n --with-ncurses --disable-locale
Patch: %f.patch
GCC: 3.1
CompileScript: ./configure %c
 make build
InstallScript: mkdir -p %i/etc/%n
 cp doc/tin.defaults %i/etc/%n
 mkdir -p %i/share/doc/%n
 head -n 13 src/active.c > %i/share/doc/%n/COPYING
 make install
DocFiles: README doc/CHANGES doc/WHATSNEW doc/TODO
#
Maintainer: Jeremy Higgs <jhiggs@iprsystems.com>
Homepage: http://www.tin.org/
License: Restrictive
Description: Simple Usenet reader
DescDetail: <<
tin is a full-screen, simple, Usenet newsreader, supporting the viewing of threads in newsgroups. This package provides the current version from the stable branch.
<<
DescPackaging: <<
ConfigureParams places files in correct places; manpages placed in correct direcotires, enables nntp-only, defines defaults dir, enables ncurses interface, and disables locale.
InstallScript creates necessary directories, copies tin.defaults file to root directory, and adds copyright notice.
<<
DescPort: <<
Changes to src/ directory provided by Mark Nowiasz add support for non-US-ASCII posts by using CoreFoundation libraries. Changes to src/Makefile.in file disable building and linking of bundled pcre source, instead using Fink-provided version of pcre.
<<
DescUsage: Local spool news reading is currently not enabled.



